title: Pocket profiles: Your club’s new players
text:
Pocket profiles: Your club’s new players following the 2015 AFL trade period Riley Beveridge FOX SPORTS Pocket profiles: Your club’s new players following the 2015 AFL trade period Riley Beveridge FOX SPORTS Final day of trade period wrap up 2:12 
AFL: As the trade period has officially finished, Neroli Meadows takes a look at all of the changes that were made. October 22nd 2015 a day ago /video/video.news.com.au/Sport/AFL/News/ 
A TOTAL of 45 players moved clubs in the nine days of the trade period, with each team making at least one new acquisition. 
So, what do you know about your side’s newest players? 
Fox Footy takes a statistical look at the men who found new homes this October and analyses what they will add to your system. Paul Seedsman spent the majority of the second half of the season in the VFL. Picture: David Smith. Jed Lamb kicked 43 goals in the NEAFL last season. Cats list manager Stephen Wells worked his magic again this off-season. Picture: Nigel Hallett. Jake Melksham is now a Melbourne player. Picture: Wayne Ludbey. Chris Yarran was dropped throughout the season from Carlton’s best side. Picture: Alex Coppel. 1 of n
